---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About" description="What digsdeeper is and how it fits alongside Jean Lucas Lima's other surfaces.">
	<section class="container">
		<header class="page-head">
			<span class="eyebrow">About</span>
			<h1>About digsdeeper</h1>
			<p class="gloss">Serious essays, working notes, and investigations about software, strategy, AI, systems, and technology culture.</p>
		</header>

		<div class="prose measure">
			<p>
				<strong>digsdeeper</strong> is Jean Lucas Lima's site for serious essays, working notes, and investigations about software, strategy, AI, systems, and technology culture.
			</p>
			<p>
				It is built to keep arguments readable, connected, and revisable over time. The goal is not volume. The goal is cumulative value — ideas that need room, structure, and memory.
			</p>
			<p>
				The site is not for daily news, personal updates, or project dumps. Those belong elsewhere.
			</p>

			<h2>Where else to find Jean</h2>
			<ul>
				<li><a href="https://jeanlucas.me">jeanlucas.me</a> — canonical identity and public map.</li>
				<li><a href="https://aleattorium.com">aleattorium.com</a> — studio for useful oddities, experiments, and artifacts.</li>
				<li><a href="https://l8p.tech">L8P.tech</a> — media, events, and tech narratives.</li>
				<li>ConfrariaTech — community infrastructure for Brazilian tech leaders.</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>How this site is organized</h2>
			<ul>
				<li><a href="/essays">Essays</a> — polished long-form arguments with a thesis.</li>
				<li><a href="/notes">Notes</a> — shorter working observations and partial arguments.</li>
				<li><a href="/series">Series</a> — long-running investigations organized around a central question.</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Subscribe</h2>
			<p>
				The site has an <a href="/feed.xml">RSS feed</a>. There is no newsletter, and there are no tracking pixels.
			</p>

			<h2>Design principle</h2>
			<blockquote>Make it feel like a place where arguments are kept long enough to become useful.</blockquote>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
